data.title: pizza73.com @ PissedConsumer
data.meta_description: Pizza 73 has 20 reviews (average rating 1.5). Consumers say: Incorrect order, Unhappy
data.text:
I placed an order and my wait time was almost an hour. Ok they are busy - no problem BUT they called when my order was suppose to have already been delivered and said my order "got stuck in the system" and I would have to reorder.

Nope ordered from elsewhere. Never again!

Maybe a discount or free would have made a difference but nothing. Lost another customer!

I ordered and my wait time was almost an hour. Ok so they are busy, no problem BUT after waiting that long and the time when the order was suppose to be here already they called and said it was stuck in the system and I could reorder.

Had it been earlier then I would have but I refused and ordered elsewhere. A discount or free items may have changed my mind.

Never again! Lost another customer

Hi my name is Jason, long time customer and father of three hungry boys last night. We ordered pizza from your Spruce Grove location as it is usually our first pic for pizza.

From my house it's a five minute walk, the pizza was two hrs getting to us and ice cold upon arrival.

My kids would not eat it unless it was microwaved. Pizza 73 failed us.

Thx for listening

I ordered a small bacon double cheeseburger pizza tonight with a golden crispy wing mean deal with a coke and ginger ale and online it said that my pizza would come here by 1:17am!!! It never came,I never got a phone call from you, and online it said that it had been delivered!!!

What a Lie!!! Now I'm left hungry thanks

On December 23rd. I ordered 40 wings and jalapeño poppers.

Delivery guy tried to give me pizza. I explained he had the wrong order, and expected him to return my proper order. He never returned. I complained to the company, and was told they'd either give me a $30 store credit, or a partial refund.

Refund minus delivery fee and taxes. I excepted the refund, but never received my refund after 12 days. And once again. I'm getting the run around.

Never again! Bloody thrives!

Hello I had ordered a medium pepperoni and bacon pizza, 2 500 ml pops one was suppose to be Coke not diet ,

The pizza was very doughy and I am sorry to complain. But the chicken popcorn was plain when they were suppose to be hot .

I love pizza 73 this time I would like money back or a new order of the same tho regular Coca-Cola , pizza pep and bacon hot sauce as base sauce , and maybe the chicken popcorn with buffulo please ? I am sorry to complain bur i can give the diet back to you the pizza and chicken kids got into theres 4 pieces and 7 chickens left but we like the spicy so if thats possible

I placed a pickup order online. When I got my food home they had messed up one of my pizzas.

I called in and the offered to replace a large half and half with a small pizza but refused to deliver it to me forcing me to go pick it up. A few minutes later they called me back and informed me I had to pack up ALL the pizza I had just brought home to feed my family and drag it back out in the cold (it was all in one box) and to the store with me to prove that they messed up.

Worst customer service ever. I will never order from there again.

I ordered 2 medium pizzas from Tudor Glen shop they got the order wrong. I asked for 2 medium and got one medium and one large.

On the large they was only one pepperoni slice on each slice of pizza. Giving me a ten dollar credit doesn't do it for me.

I want to know what action you're going to take to see that this doesn't keep happening. I'm tempted to take this to social media to see what reaction I will get.

The reason why I am writing this two orders have came I order one the first person came at 1:10 am with a messed up order I paid for my order before you took everything out of the bag one can of Coca-Cola was destroyed and he took two sandwiches out chicken sandwiches I mean after I paid for the order

I was not impressed with the service that particular delivery because he told me that he gave my order to somebody else I paid cash or that particular order the receipt itself was destroyed from the can of Coca-Cola that was broken open....

I have waited for 2 hours for my order when I called customer service I was told that the order I placed at location close to my residence where I live which is on 82nd Street and 123rd Ave

And then the other person came at 1:26 a.m. where I paid again the discounted price of $11.75 which I used debit for that one the date stamped on the receipt is 12/32/2021
